events.name: Transition to Electromobility and LIB Development
events.wd_label: Transition to Electromobility and LIB Development
events.wd_description: As the global transport sector shifts towards electromobility, the value chain for raw materials used in lithium-ion battery (LIB) development becomes critical. This study assesses criticality aspects of LIB cells to identify supply risks and inform battery technology development.
events.description: As the global transport sector shifts towards electromobility, the value chain for raw materials used in lithium-ion battery (LIB) development becomes critical. This study assesses criticality aspects of LIB cells to identify supply risks and inform battery technology development.

events.name: Value Chain Criticality Assessment
events.wd_description: The study uses the ESSENZ method to systematically assess eleven criticality aspects of ten LIB cells, evaluating the criticality scores by aggregating the scores of eleven constituent value chains.

events.name: Nickel Cobalt Aluminium Oxide
events.description: NCA batteries are used by Tesla in their electric vehicles due to their high energy density and stability. These batteries contain nickel, cobalt, and aluminum as their primary components and are known for their high performance and long life span, making them suitable for the high demands of electric vehicles.

events.name: Lithium Iron Phosphate
events.description: LFP batteries are another type of battery used by Tesla, particularly valued for their safety and longevity. These batteries contain lithium, iron, and phosphate, offering a lower energy density compared to NCA batteries but with a longer cycle life and better thermal stability, making them a preferred choice for certain Tesla models and applications.

events.name: Sodium ion Batteries Comparison
events.description: Sodium-ion batteries (SIBs) use sodium ions as charge carriers, offering several advantages over lithium-ion batteries, including lower cost, better safety characteristics, and similar power delivery characteristics. However, they have a lower energy density compared to lithium-ion batteries. Sodium's natural abundance and the use of more abundant iron-based materials, as opposed to cobalt, copper, and nickel, further enhance the appeal of sodium-ion batteries.

events.name: Highest Unit Cost in Scenario A
events.description: Scenario A shows the highest unit cost due to the Advanced Warehouse being located 20 km away from the plant, requiring dedicated trips and a buffer warehouse at the production site.

events.name: Space Constraints in Scenario B
events.description: Scenario B is cheaper because the Advanced Warehouse is inside the production site, requiring only a 1 km trip. However, it faces space constraints, needing redesign of the plant layout to host the new warehouse.

events.name: Intermediate Cost in Scenario C
events.description: Scenario C is more expensive than Scenario B but cheaper than Scenario A. The Advanced Warehouse is located 20 km away, and batteries are directly sent to the production line without buffer storage.

events.name: Cheapest and Riskiest in Scenario D
events.description: Scenario D is the cheapest due to the direct connection between the supplier plant and the production line, with no Advanced Warehouse and fewer handling activities. However, it is the most risky as the supplier is 2,000 km away, making it susceptible to supply interruptions.

events.description: Traceability refers to the ability to track the source of materials used in the battery supply chain to ensure ethical sourcing.

events.name: Supply Chain Diversification
events.description: Supply chain diversification involves spreading out production capacity to multiple countries to avoid over-reliance on a single nation.

events.name: South American Projects
events.wd_description: New lithium projects in South America are contributing significant supply to the global market, potentially easing supply constraints.
events.description: New lithium projects in South America are contributing significant supply to the global market, potentially easing supply constraints.

events.name: African Projects
events.wd_description: Lithium projects in Africa are expected to bring additional supply to the market, contributing to the overall production increase.
events.description: Lithium projects in Africa are expected to bring additional supply to the market, contributing to the overall production increase.

events.name: Government Policies
events.wd_description: Changes in government policies in key lithium-producing countries can significantly affect the market and supply chains.
events.description: Changes in government policies in key lithium-producing countries can significantly affect the market and supply chains.

events.name: Political Stability
events.wd_description: Political instability in regions with major lithium projects could disrupt production and impact global supply.
events.description: Political instability in regions with major lithium projects could disrupt production and impact global supply.

events.name: Grants Operation
events.wd_description: The Grants open pit at Finniss is the primary focus of current operations, with activities aimed at increasing production efficiency.
events.description: The Grants open pit at Finniss is the primary focus of current operations, with activities aimed at increasing production efficiency.

events.name: Production Expansion
events.wd_description: Efforts are being made to expand production capacity at Finniss, with an emphasis on maximizing output and optimizing costs.
events.description: Efforts are being made to expand production capacity at Finniss, with an emphasis on maximizing output and optimizing costs.

events.name: Price Forecasting
events.description: This event captures the forecasting of lithium prices based on current and projected market conditions, including supply and demand dynamics.

events.name: Supply Demand Analysis
events.description: This event reflects the detailed analysis of supply and demand trends affecting the lithium market, including production capacities and market needs.

events.name: Project Viability
events.description: This event assesses the long-term viability of various lithium projects under changing market conditions, including financial and operational considerations.

events.name: Supply Chain Resilience
events.description: This event captures measures and strategies taken to enhance the resilience of the lithium supply chain in the face of geopolitical and market risks.

events.name: Impact reduction
events.wd_description: The study shows that environmental and social impacts can be significantly reduced in many scenarios compared to the benchmark.

events.name: EU Battery Regulation
events.description: Specific regulation enforcing these requirements.

events.name: Life Cycle Sustainability Assessment
events.description: Methodology for assessing sustainability.

events.name: Use phase inclusion
events.description: Future studies should expand system boundaries to include the use phase as a source for material that must be recycled.

events.name: Battery production inclusion
events.description: Battery production should also be considered within the expanded system boundaries to derive comprehensive recommendations

events.name: Pyrometallurgical recycling route
events.description: More recycling routes, such as the pyrometallurgical route, should be considered, as different companies use different recycling methods

events.name: Combination of recycling routes
events.description: Combinations of various recycling routes should be evaluated to provide more comprehensive recommendations.

events.name: Spatial concentration of waste batteries
events.description: The scale of recycling facilities should be varied to recommend the optimal size based on the spatial concentration of waste batteries.

events.name: Environmental sustainability assessment
events.description: Complex environmental sustainability assessment is required to ensure the viability of the circular supply chain for EV batteries.

events.name: Economic viability assessment
events.description: Economic viability assessment is critical for designing and developing the circular supply chain.

events.name: Internet of Things Integration
events.description: IoT plays a major role in managing data for battery management and delivering optimal performance.

events.name: Minimizing CO2 emissions
events.description: The bi-objective mixed-integer linear programming model aims to minimize total costs and CO2 emissions.

events.name: Simulation algorithm for validation
events.description: A simulation algorithm examines the effectiveness of the proposed model through simulated problems, ensuring accuracy and reliability.

events.name: Fuzzy multi objective method
events.description: The bi-objective optimization model uses a fuzzy multi-objective method to handle uncertainties and improve decision-making.

events.name: Cobalt free
events.description: LFP batteries do not use cobalt, which is a key characteristic differentiating them from other lithium-ion batteries.

events.name: Specific energy comparison
events.description: Include detailed comparison specific energy values of CATL's LFP batteries (125 Wh/kg, possibly 160 Wh/kg), BYD's LFP batteries (150 Wh/kg), and NMC batteries (over 300 Wh/kg), as well as Panasonic’s NCA batteries (around 260 Wh/kg).

events.name: Patent expiration impact
events.description: Patents for LFP technology started expiring in 2022, leading to increased production and expected surpassing of NMC batteries by 2028.

events.name: Production dominance of Chinese manufacturers
events.description: Chinese manufacturers hold a near monopoly on LFP battery production.

events.name: China Role in Battery Supply
events.description: China is the main provider of synthetic and natural graphite, refined cobalt, and lithium-ion cells and batteries.
